Controls._HtmlContent:
Regular TDS

 

- Click on the "START" button to start the chronometer and enable the TDS buttons. The chronometer is required to display elapsed time or to set a maximum time (40 seconds here).

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention and becomes "dominant", click on the TDS button corresponding to this  attribute. This attribute remains dominant until a new one is clicked.

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "STOP" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
Regular TDS, sample /SpecialLabel/

Hold-down TDS

 

- Click on the "START" button to enable the TDS buttons.

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention and becomes "dominant", click and hold down the TDS button corresponding to this  attribute. When the TDS button is released, the attribute is no longer dominant and you should click on another dominant attribute, if any.

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "STOP" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
TDS with no dominance (hold-down), sample: /SpecialLabel/

No dominance TDS

 

- Click on the "START" button to enable the TDS buttons.

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention and becomes "dominant", click on the TDS button corresponding to this  attribute. The attribute will remains dominant until you click again on the TDS button (no dominance) or on another TDS button (new dominance).

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "Next" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
TDS with no dominance (click-unclick), sample: /SpecialLabel/

Fading TDS

 

- When there is no "START", the chronometer starts when the screen is displayed.

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention and becomes "dominant", click on the TDS button corresponding to this  attribute. The attribute will remains dominant until you click on a new attribute or until the "dominance duration limit" (5 seconds in this demo) is reached.

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "Next" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
TDS with no dominance (fading), sample: /SpecialLabel/

TDS with pictures

 

- Click on the "START" button to start the chronometer and enable the TDS buttons. The chronometer is required to display elapsed time or to set a maximum time (40 seconds here).

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention and becomes "dominant", click on the picture corresponding to this  attribute. This attribute remains dominant until a new one is clicked.

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "STOP" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
Regular TDS, sample /SpecialLabel/

Dual TDS

 

- Click on the "START" button to start the chronometer and enable the TDS buttons in each sensory modality (aroma/texture). The chronometer is required to display elapsed time or to set a maximum time (40 seconds here).

- Each time and attribute triggers your attention in a sensory modality and becomes "dominant", click on the button corresponding to this  attribute. This attribute remains dominant until a new one is clicked in the sensory modality (two attributes belonging to different sensory modalities can be dominant at the same time).

- When you no longer perceive any sensation, click on the "STOP" button: the chronometer is stopped and the TDS buttons are disabled.
Dual TDS, sample /SpecialLabel/
